Cape Town-based Sygnia has shut down its hedge fund products, which had been running for around 13 years. CEO of the asset manager Magda Wierzycka believes that hedge funds have not been able to deliver on the promise of capital preservation despite charging hefty performance fees. Ryk van Niekerk speaks to Wierzycka on the Moneyweb @ Midday show about Sygnia’s decision and view on the hedge fund industry as a whole.